**Project:** SNAPKITTYWEST -- Sovereign Compute Architecture
**Supersedes:** Sovereign Source License v1.0

---

## Preamble

The Sovereign Compute substrate is free. The formed works belong to their makers. No one owns the substrate. The registry records what exists and who made it. The marks signal what has been verified. Nothing more is asserted, granted, or restricted by this License than these propositions require.

This License is a family of three independent instruments:

- **Part II** -- Public Domain Dedication (unilateral, no counter-signature required)
- **Part III** -- Sovereign Registry and Attribution (bilateral, upon Declaration of Formation)
- **Part VII** -- Sovereign Certification Marks (bilateral, upon certification application)

A party may rely on Part II without being subject to Parts III or VII. Parts III and VII apply only to parties who affirmatively engage with the Sovereign Registry or the Certification Mark system.

---

## PART I -- DEFINITIONS

### Section 1. Definitions

**1.1 Core Definitions**

| Term | Definition |
|------|-----------|
| **Work** | The software, documentation, mathematical proofs, and associated files licensed under this agreement |
| **Sovereign Substrate** | The mathematical and computational foundations (Goldilocks field arithmetic, Banach contraction mappings, WORM chain protocols, multi-witness verification) |
| **Formed Work** | A specific implementation, configuration, or deployment built upon the Sovereign Substrate |
| **Maker** | Any person or entity that creates a Formed Work |
| **Bound Work** | A Formed Work that has been registered with the Sovereign Registry |
| **Sovereign Registry** | The append-only ledger recording Formed Works, their Makers, and their verification status |
| **Certification Mark** | The visual marks (textual, graphical, or digital) signifying a specific Certification Tier |
| **Certification Tier** | A level of verification (Tier I through IV) indicating the degree of formal verification achieved |
| **Operator** | Bel Esprit D'Accord Trust, the entity maintaining the Sovereign Registry |
| **Constitutional Core** | The Sovereign Substrate as governed by Part II of this License |
| **Commercial Use** | Use of the Work in products, services, or activities primarily intended for financial gain |
| **AI/ML Training** | Use of the Work to train, fine-tune, evaluate, or benchmark machine learning models |
| **Institutional Body** | Any government agency, corporation, non-profit organization, or institutional entity |

**1.2 Certification Tiers**

| Tier | Name | Requirement | Mark |
|------|------|-------------|------|
| I | **Witnessed** | 3-witness consensus (NT + ALG + IT) | `Ω·I` |
| II | **Sealed** | WORM chain seal + audit trail | `Ω·II` |
| III | **Sovereign** | Machine-checked proof (Lean 4 / WASM verifier) | `Ω·III` |
| IV | **Constitutional** | Full boot protocol + self-verification closure | `Ω·IV` |

