## PART III -- SOVEREIGN REGISTRY AND ATTRIBUTION

### Section 3. Declaration of Formation

**3.1** A Maker who wishes to register a Bound Work files a Declaration of Formation with the Sovereign Registry, containing:

| Field | Required | Description |
|-------|----------|-------------|
| Maker Identity | Yes | Legal name or pseudonym of the Maker |
| Work Description | Yes | Title, version, and brief description of the Formed Work |
| Substrate Dependencies | Yes | Which components of the Sovereign Substrate are used |
| Purpose and Context | Yes | Declared purpose and context of use |
| Attribution Chain | Yes | Complete provenance of all inherited works |
| Witness Statement | Yes | Statement that the Maker has verified the work to their stated Tier |

**3.2** The Declaration becomes a permanent, immutable record in the Sovereign Registry upon filing.

**3.3** The Maker warrants that all statements in the Declaration are materially true and complete.

**3.4** A Maker who files a Declaration containing material false statements of attribution:
- (a) Immediately loses all Certification Mark privileges
- (b) Forfeits the right to represent the Work as verified or certified
- (c) Must remove all Certification Marks within thirty (30) days
- (d) Remains bound by all other provisions of this License

### Section 4. Sovereign Registry Operations

**4.1** The Sovereign Registry is maintained as an append-only WORM chain with Ed25519 sealing.

**4.2** The Registry records:
- (a) All Declarations of Formation
- (b) All Certification applications and determinations
- (c) All mark license grants and terminations
- (d) All Technical Review Panel determinations

**4.3** Registry records are public and queryable. The Registry serves the commons. It is not a participant in the market.

**4.4** The Operator does not:
- (a) Charge a fee for Tier I or Tier II standing
- (b) Charge a fee as a percentage of any Maker's revenue
- (c) Receive royalties from any Bound Work
- (d) Take equity in any enterprise that files a Declaration
- (e) Participate in any commercial transaction between a Maker and the Maker's customers

### Section 5. Patent Provisions

**5.1 No Patent Claims on Substrate.** No Maker who files a Declaration of Formation may file any patent application covering any portion of the Sovereign Substrate.

**5.2** Any patent application filed in violation of Section 5.1 is automatically assigned to the Operator upon filing, to the extent such assignment is enforceable.

**5.3** If a Maker files a patent application covering the Sovereign Substrate:
- (a) All Certification Mark privileges terminate immediately
- (b) All rights granted under Parts III and VII terminate immediately
- (c) The Maker must remove all Certification Marks within thirty (30) days

**5.4 No Patent Litigation Against Substrate Users.** No Maker who files a Declaration of Formation may initiate patent litigation against any person for that person's good-faith use of the Sovereign Substrate.

**5.5** Initiation of patent litigation in violation of Section 5.4 results in immediate termination of all rights under Parts III and VII.

### Section 6. Attribution Requirements

**6.1** All Bound Works must include the following attribution:

```
Built on Sovereign Source -- Bel Esprit D'Accord Trust
(c) 2026 Ahmad Ali Parr -- snapkittywest.github.io
Sovereign Registry: [Registry ID]
Certification Tier: [Tier Level]
```

**6.2** Derivative Works distributed publicly must be released under:
- Sovereign Source License v2.0, or later version
- With full attribution chain preserved

**6.3** All redistributions must preserve:
- WORM chain seals
- Cryptographic hashes
- Audit trail entries
- Certification Mark provenance

