## PART IV -- SOVEREIGN CERTIFICATION MARKS

### Section 7. Certification Mark System

**7.1 Mark Ownership.** The Certification Marks are owned by the Operator. The Operator grants limited use rights under the conditions of this Part.

**7.2 Mark Classes.**

| Mark | Tier | Meaning |
|------|------|---------|
| `Ω·I` | Tier I -- Witnessed | 3-witness consensus achieved (NT + ALG + IT) |
| `Ω·II` | Tier II -- Sealed | WORM chain seal + immutable audit trail |
| `Ω·III` | Tier III -- Sovereign | Machine-checked proof (Lean 4 / WASM verifier) |
| `Ω·IV` | Tier IV -- Constitutional | Full boot protocol + self-verification closure |

**7.3 Mark Integrity.** The Certification Marks are integrity signals. They represent a factual claim about verification status. Misuse of the marks undermines the trust infrastructure for all Makers.

### Section 8. Prohibited Mark Use

**8.1** No person or entity may:

> **(a)** Display any Certification Mark in connection with a Bound Work that has not achieved the corresponding Certification Tier

> **(b)** Represent to any third party that a Bound Work has been Sovereign Certified by Bel Esprit D'Accord Trust in the absence of a valid, current Certification Tier record in the Sovereign Registry

> **(c)** Use any mark, name, logo, or representation that is confusingly similar to the Certification Marks in connection with any representation about Constitutional Core conformance

**8.2** The prohibition in Section 8.1 applies regardless of whether the use is:
- (a) Commercial or non-commercial
- (b) Digital or physical
- (c) Public or private (to the extent the representation reaches third parties)

**8.3** A Maker may operate a computational service using Constitutional Core mathematics without Tier III certification. What such a Maker may not do is represent that service as conformant, certified, or verified by Bel Esprit D'Accord Trust, or use the Certification Marks in connection with it.

**8.4** The distinction is between the service (unaffected by this License) and the representation (governed by this Part and by trademark law).

### Section 9. Certification Standards

**9.1** A Maker who offers a Represented Computational Service must hold at minimum Tier III Certification for the declared Purpose and Context within which the service is offered.

**9.2 Certification Requirements by Tier:**

| Tier | Requirement | Verification Method |
|------|-------------|---------------------|
| I | 3-witness consensus on all claims | Automated (CI pipeline) |
| II | WORM chain seal + immutable audit | Automated (CI pipeline) |
| III | Machine-checked proof | Lean 4 / WASM verifier / formal proof |
| IV | Full boot closure + self-verification | Constitutional boot protocol + meta-proof |

**9.3 Technical Review Panel.** The Operator may convene a Technical Review Panel to evaluate certification applications for Tiers III and IV. The Panel's determination is final.

### Section 10. Mark License Grant

**10.1** Subject to the requirements of Section 8 and the applicable Certification Tier holding, the Operator grants to each Maker holding an applicable Certification Tier a limited, non-exclusive, non-transferable, revocable license to use the corresponding Certification Mark solely:

> **(a)** In connection with the Bound Work identified in the Maker's Declaration of Formation

> **(b)** Within the Purpose and Context declared in that filing

> **(c)** In a manner consistent with the Operator's published mark usage guidelines

**10.2** The mark license is co-extensive with the Certification Tier. When the Tier lapses, the mark license terminates.

**10.3** The Maker may not sublicense, assign, or transfer the mark license without prior written consent of the Operator.

### Section 11. Mark License Termination

**11.1** The mark license granted in Section 10 terminates automatically if:

> **(a)** The Maker's Certification Tier lapses or is withdrawn due to non-renewal, violation, or Technical Review Panel determination

> **(b)** The Maker files a patent application covering Sovereign Substrate mathematics (Section 5.2)

> **(c)** The Maker initiates patent litigation against another person's good-faith Sovereign Substrate use (Section 5.4)

> **(d)** The Maker's Declaration of Formation is found to contain material false statements of attribution (Section 3.4)

**11.2** Termination requires the Maker to immediately cease all use of the Certification Marks and remove them from all materials within thirty (30) days.

**11.3** Upon termination:
- (a) All representations using Certification Marks become false and must be retracted
- (b) The Maker's Bound Work remains in the Registry with a "Terminated" annotation
- (c) The Maker's right to re-certify is not impaired (they may reapply)

### Section 12. Registry Economics

**12.1** The Operator accepts voluntary contributions from Makers and the public in support of registry operations, certification infrastructure, and long-term archival stewardship.

**12.2** The Operator does not:

> **(a)** Charge a fee for Tier I or Tier II standing

> **(b)** Charge a fee as a percentage of any Maker's revenue

> **(c)** Receive royalties from any Bound Work

> **(d)** Take equity in any enterprise that files a Declaration

> **(e)** Participate in any commercial transaction between a Maker and the Maker's customers

**12.3** Certification audit contributions (Tiers III and IV) are calibrated to cover actual audit costs. Excess contributions fund subsidized certification for nonprofit and academic Makers and the long-term stewardship endowment.

**12.4** The Operator makes the same amount regardless of whether a certified Bound Work generates zero revenue or transforms an industry. The registry serves the commons. It is not a participant in the market.

