## PART VI -- GENERAL PROVISIONS

### Section 16. Three Instruments, One License Family

**16.1** Parts II, III, and VII of this License are legally independent instruments. Part II requires no counter-signature and is effective as a unilateral dedication. Parts III and VII are effective as between the Operator and each Maker upon the Maker's submission of a Declaration of Formation or application for Certification, respectively.

**16.2** A party may rely on Part II (the public domain dedication) without being subject to Parts III or VII. Parts III and VII apply only to parties who affirmatively engage with the Sovereign Registry or the Certification Mark system.

### Section 17. Stewardship and Versioning

**17.1** The Operator may publish revised versions of Parts III and VII of this License. Revised versions will bear a new version number.

**17.2** Makers who filed Declarations of Formation under an earlier version continue to hold their rights under the version in effect at the time of filing; they may elect to migrate to a later version by filing an Amended Declaration.

**17.3** No revision of this License may diminish or condition the public domain dedication of Part II.

### Section 18. Severability

**18.1** If any provision of this License is held unenforceable, the remaining provisions continue in full force. The unenforceable provision is modified to the minimum extent required to make it enforceable while preserving the parties' evident intent.

### Section 19. No Warranty

**19.1** THE SOVEREIGN SUBSTRATE IS MADE AVAILABLE AS-IS. THE OPERATOR MAKES NO REPRESENTATIONS OR WARRANTIES OF MATHEMATICAL CORRECTNESS, FITNESS FOR ANY PARTICULAR PURPOSE, OR NON-INFRINGEMENT OF THIRD-PARTY INTELLECTUAL PROPERTY RIGHTS.

### Section 20. Limitation of Liability

**20.1** THE OPERATOR'S AGGREGATE LIABILITY TO ANY MAKER IN CONNECTION WITH THIS LICENSE AND THE SOVEREIGN REGISTRY SHALL NOT EXCEED THE TOTAL VOLUNTARY CONTRIBUTIONS RECEIVED FROM THAT MAKER IN THE TWELVE MONTHS PRECEDING THE CLAIM.

### Section 21. Governing Interpretation Principle

**21.1** In any proceeding concerning the interpretation of this License, the following principle governs:

> The substrate is always free.
> The formed work always belongs to its Maker.
> No one owns the substrate.
> The formed work may be owned, licensed, patented, published, or kept private -- entirely at the Maker's election.
> The registry records what exists and who made it.
> The marks signal what has been verified.
> Nothing more is asserted, granted, or restricted by this License than these propositions require.

### Section 22. Governing Law and Dispute Resolution

**22.1** This License is governed by the laws of the State of [Bel Esprit D'Accord Trust jurisdiction], without regard to conflicts-of-law principles.

**22.2** Disputes between the Operator and any Maker arising under this License are subject to binding arbitration under the Commercial Arbitration Rules of the American Arbitration Association, with venue in [City, State].

